Sextiles: this was not the formal announcement (professio) on Cicero's part of his intention of standing fo: the consulship, as the latter would be made on the day on which notice of the election was given, i.e. three nunainae, or 17 days, before the day of the election. Cicero speaks of Caesonius in a very different way in Verr. i. 29 homo in rebus iudicandis spectatus et cognitus. — Aquilium: sc. competitorem sore. C.
